    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large spiked hooks, usually square-angled, that are driven into the rafter during roof thatching in order to secure courses of thatch as the thatcher works.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
